Hi Marcus,

Great kick-off session on Friday. Summarising key decisions for the record.

SAMPLE: n=1,180 respondents, nationally representative adult sample. Fieldwork planned for April 2023.

SEGMENTATION (core variable: purchase intent after concept exposure):
- probable_trialists: respondents who "would definitely" or "would probably" buy NovaSkinX
- non_probable: would not buy
- buy_regularly: already buy skincare products regularly (3+ times per month)
- buy_occasionally: occasional skincare buyers (1-2 times per month)
- try_once: would try once but not commit to repeat purchase

INDEX CONVENTION: An index of 100 = total sample average. Above 100 = over-indexing.
Example: probable_trialists_spend_index of 143 means probable trialists spend 43% more on skincare than the average respondent.

VARIABLE NAMING: {segment}_{metric}_{measure}. Examples:
- probable_trialists_spend_avg = average monthly EUR spend on skincare among probable trialists
- buy_regularly_share_of_wallet_share = share of personal care budget for regular buyers
- total_sample_preference_sample_size = sample size for preference in total sample

SC = skincare category. Variable sc_brand_awareness tracks aided awareness per brand across the competitive set.

Questionnaire covers: demographics, category behaviour, daily skincare routine, needs assessment (50+ items), concept evaluation (NovaSkinX), and competition (15 skincare categories rated 0-10).

Draft questionnaire by Thursday. Please review the brand list — current set uses fictional placeholder brands (brand_a_mass_market, brand_b_derma, brand_c_ingredient_led, brand_d_natural) rather than real brand names for safety.

